post_text:
SWA Spirit Night - TONIGHT
Join us this evening from 4PM - 9PM at Daddy D's BBQ in Fuquay-Varina for our first SWA Spirit Night of the new school year! We will have a Spirit Night at various local restaurants once a month this school year. Come out and enjoy some delicious BBQ to celebrate the #bestfirstdayofschool!

You have the option to Dine in, Take-out or use their Drive thru (does not include third party delivery, grub hub or doordash)! This event is open to the public so please tell your friends, family and neighbors. A portion of the proceeds will be donated back to our school.

Check out their new video to preview what they are cooking up!
https://www.facebook.com/watch/?v=746131282830815
Our next Spirit Night will be held at Anna's Pizzeria in downtown Fuquay-Varina in September.

Join us this evening for our SWA Town Hall Meeting via Zoom.
Dr. Tom Miller, SWA Interim Head of School, will be sharing details and highlights regarding the SWA RETURN TO LEARN PLAN and will address the key themes and concerns in regards to student learning.

DISCUSSION TOPICS:
- Middle and High School Drafted Schedule
- Learning Platform and Instructional Methods
- Attendance Process
- Communication Plans
- Estimated Timeline to Plan B/Hybrid learning

Parents and students will be permitted to ask specific questions in the chat box. The meeting will run from 6:00PM - 7:00PM.

Any questions not addressed will be added to a FAQ document on the school's website or will be addressed at the next Town Hall Meeting.

Please use the below Zoom link to join the meeting:
https://us02web.zoom.us/j/4850136618

Meeting ID: 485 013 6618

CONGRATULATIONS to Emma Karsen (7th grade) who has been invited to attend the 2021 Presidential Inauguration Alumni Program in Washington, D.C. Emma has been invited for this historic opportunity as an alumna of the National Youth Leadership Forum: Pathways to STEM.

The event is being held in celebration of the 59th Inauguration of the President and Vice President of the United States. This momentous occasion, full of ceremony and traditions, is truly a once-in-a-lifetime experience.

This is truly an honor and we are all so proud!

Lands' End Starboard Scholarship Winner!
We proudly announce that Tyson Greenbaum, 7th grade, has been selected to received a $10,000 Lands' End Starboard Scholarship Award! A limit of 3000 applications were accepted for this scholarship, and only one student per grade, grades 6-12, received this award. Tyson is one of only 7 recipients!
Congratulations, Tyson! We are SO proud of you!!

post_text:
SWA's 3rd Annual Fashion Show is scheduled for November 23rd at the Fuquay Varina Cultural Arts Theater. This year our Preshow Vendor Fair will be OPEN TO THE PUBLIC!
Come out for an evening of food, friends, shopping and fashion while supporting our SWA Lion Crusade Fund.

The SWA Lion Crusade Fund is used to help pay the for the costs of our after school programs including: Athletics, Clubs, Organizations and Academic Competitions. Charter schools DO NOT receive as much funding as the traditional public schools, therefore our families must take on the cost of these programs. This additional cost is difficult for so many of our families and tough choices need to be made. The ultimate goal for this fund is to ELIMINATE the fees that our families pay in order for their child to participate in these activities.

Contact Mrs. Neumann for more information at jennifer.neumann@swake.org.

post_text:
We would like to take this opportunity to thank our SWA Lion Crusade partners for their support this school year. This fund was created with the goal of helping to support our SWA Clubs, Athletics and Academic Competitions. These local businesses with their generous support have helped our students to be able to compete in numerous Academic Competitions where we have placed and even won at the state level. The funds have also provided new sports equipment for our Volleyball team who won their 1st State Championship and our Middle School Girls Basketball team who won their conference with an undefeated season.
If you own a business or your company would be interested in becoming a Lion Crusade partner to help support our after school programs, please contact Mrs. Neumann at jneumann@swake.org. There are various partnership levels starting at only $100. Your donations are tax deductible and will help us to be able to continue to offer these wonderful opportunities to our students.

post_text:
We would like to welcome Carolina Insurance Alliance as one of our newest Lion Crusade partners.
Carolina Insurance Alliance always strives to provide their clients with the best possible service, at the best possible value for their auto, home, life, or business insurance needs. They are not a captive insurance agency, so they have the freedom and the ability to place their clients coverage with multiple companies, based on who can provide the best value at the time. So if you have a spike in insurance premiums, but appreciate what they do for you as an agency, they can do the shopping for you in order to provide you with multiple quotes and coverage options to satisfy any of your needs.
Jason Thompson, founder and local agent for the company is an SWA parent and was featured in our SWAG Bags at our recent Glitz and Glamour Fashion Show.
You can find more information about this company on their Website: www.carolinainsurancealliance.com/index.html
or visit them on Facebook Carolina Insurance Alliance. Welcome to the SWA Lion Crusade Family...

Our camp programs, which are open to the public offer children the chance to participate in a variety of weekly fun and engaging programs.

The program instructors are creative and dedicated SWA Staff members who will challenge and inspire students to reach their full potential in an area that they are passionate about.

This opportunity will provide your child with an exciting hands-on learning experience while empowering them with skills for their future. We are offering: Theater, Basketball, Science (STEAM) and Cheer camps. Camps are $150 per week and run from 8:00 am - 2:30 pm with early drop off at 7:30 am (additional $10 fee). We offer sibling discounts and payment plans.

Please email Jennifer Neumann, SWA Camp Director at jneumann@swake.org for more camp details and registration forms.

post_text:
As you may be aware, there was a story that aired on ABC 11 today in regards to a situation that happened here last month. It was dealt with and handled immediately by administration when it happened. The following formal statement has been sent to the news station this afternoon.

The administration of SWA was made aware of a situation that happened in a middle school classroom last month in regards to a teacher taping a student’s mouth with masking tape. This was handled quickly and seriously by contacting parents and meeting with the teacher. Although inappropriate, the teacher's actions were not of a malicious intent. The teacher was placed on a disciplinary action plan for the remainder of the school year. The parents were contacted in regards to what disciplinary action took place and were extended an invitation weeks ago with dates and times to meet with both the teacher and administration. No grievances were filed and no other instances have taken place.

Mr. David Thomas
Principal
Southern Wake Academy
(919) 567-9955 ext. 4207

We would like to Welcome Fritz Orthodontics as one of our newest SWA Lion Crusade Partners.
Located just down the road from our school in Holly Springs, Dr. Kristen Fritz and Dr. Cliff Wilson are proud to offer outstanding orthodontic care for the entire family in a clean and friendly atmosphere. Through their cutting-edge technology, state-of-the-art equipment and patient-oriented focus, they dedicate their practice to improving the health, appearance and self-confidence of each and every patient they serve.
Dr. Fritz and her wonderful team enjoy participating in community events, they will be presenting for the 2nd year at our upcoming Career Day event and were featured in our SWAG Bags at our recent Glitz & Glamour Fashion Show.
They are getting ready to move into their beautiful NEW office building located at 363 Village Walk Drive in Holly Springs. For more information or to schedule an appointment visit their website at https://www.fritzorthodontics.com/ or like them on Facebook: Fritz Orthodontics. Welcome to the SWA Family...

The Serve & Share club, whose members range from 6th-12th grade, focuses on helping kids find ways to serve in their community. They’ve made holiday cards & clipped coupons for the military; crafted pet toys and fleece blankets for an animal shelter; birthday cards & Valentines for the elderly; helped sort food drive items at the local food pantry; hosted custodian appreciation, and more.
Papa Murphy’s has kindly agreed to host a Spirit Night at their Fuquay-Varina location to help use raise funds to purchase materials for our service projects.
If you have a hankering for some great pizza today (2/6/19), please consider heading over to Papa Murphy’s for a pie or 2, and thank them for supporting the kids in the SWA Serve & Share club.
Thank you, Mrs. Mangum..

post_text: Another amazing opportunity for our SWA students...
shared_text:
Today in the Quay
January 17, 2019 at 10:06 PM ·

Today was an exciting day for this page. I met with Southern Wake Academy and the school has decided to offer writing for Today in the Quay as part of their annual journalism curriculum. Students will now be writers for the page, through their journalism elective. This will create accountability, as it will now be done through their academic program. I will be receiving two new stories shortly, and community stories will now be regularly received from the school. I'm excited about this for the kids and I'm honored that the school would want to do this with Today in the Quay.

post_text:
We would like to welcome Seagle & Associates as our newest Lion Crusade partner.
Seagle & Associates has been in business for 33 years conducting appraisal, brokerage and contracting services. Their focus as appraisers has been commercial real estate with regards to lending, condemnation, easements and estate narratives. Their brokerage has focused on both negotiating and representing commercial, land and specialty properties as well as the occasional residential property. The construction company has worked in both the residential and commercial field of contracting. Their office is in Fuquay Varina across from Fire Station No.1. Welcome to the SWA family...

post_text:
Parnet Letter from Principal Thomas
SWA Families,

As we continue to follow the track of this massive storm, we are now being told that our area will again be getting more rain through tomorrow. The storm will be tracking north continuing to put us on the wrong side of it. The safety of our SWA family is of the utmost importance. With that being said, we will be closed on Monday, September 17. Please be safe and stay inside if at all possible.

Mr. David Thomas
Principal

Hey SWA Family! As many of you know, Google came to our school a couple months ago and beta tested a new app for our students. The app introduces augmented reality to the classroom. It is a huge resource for teachers and students to be able to show students what certain concepts look like in person. If you would look to learn more, follow the link below.

We are going to try to build some sets of devices for next year so teachers can take advantage of this app. We are asking if you have any old iPhones or Android phones that you're not using to consider donating them to the school for us to use with the Google AR app. If you have any questions just email me at rumcbride@swake.org. Please drop them off in the front office or in my room 4208.
Thanks! Mr. McBride

post_text: Congratulations on such a great season! Way to go, guys! #LionPride
shared_text:
Keith Ferreira is with Steven Oakley and 5 others.
May 10, 2018 at 8:51 AM ·

Southern Wake Academy Lions go down to Uwharrie Charter Academy Eagles in the CAASC Middle School State semi-final. The Eagles players, coaches, and fans were great hosts, and playing on their amazing field was an awesome experience. It was a pleasure to coach every player on this team. All of them worked to become better players, and they did. I look forward to seeing how they continue to grow and develop. Great season Lions. You made you coaches, family, and school proud.

We are bringing in career minded people from our community to provide students with first-hand knowledge of potential career paths. post_text:
Southern Wake Academy has started a GROW program that is 'Bringing Learning Outdoors' for our staff and students. Ms. Clifton, who started the program, has plans to build an outdoor gym and art/science lab for our students. In an effort to promote 'outdoor learning' and educate families about eco-friendly alternatives to help preserve our environment we are hosting Earth Day 2018.
This event is FREE and open to the public!
